        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 7:47PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 747 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles west of Jigger to 12 miles southwest of
Olla. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jena, Olla, Midway, Urania, Tullos, Georgetown, Nebo, Spaulding,
Standard, Rochelle, Kelly, Zenoria, and Burlington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
